<paragraph blockId="17.[159,762,1632,1948]" lastBlockId="17.[826,1429,311,1200]" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">
Morphology — Deutonymph: P-2 with one serrate seta in ventral and proximomedial position; P- 4 with strongly developed cone-shaped, projections on ventral margin, two proximal, apically bearing a denticle-like seta, one distal, apically bearing a peglike seta; P-5 claw bifurcated into two very long, slender clawlets (length: dorsal 32, ventral 25 µm) (
<figureCitation box="[834,957,416,440]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="18.[159,171,1151,1170]" captionTargetBox="[242,1346,302,1118]" captionTargetId="figure-5@18.[242,1346,302,1118]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10: Unionicola (Majumderatax) sp., deutonymph, Mekong River, Vietnam: A – idiosoma, ventral view; B-C – palp; D – I-L-5 and -6. Scale bars – 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396008" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396008/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">Figures 10</figureCitation>
B-C). Provisional genital field with two pairs of acetabula (
<figureCitation box="[1045,1180,451,475]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="18.[159,171,1151,1170]" captionTargetBox="[242,1346,302,1118]" captionTargetId="figure-5@18.[242,1346,302,1118]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10: Unionicola (Majumderatax) sp., deutonymph, Mekong River, Vietnam: A – idiosoma, ventral view; B-C – palp; D – I-L-5 and -6. Scale bars – 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396008" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396008/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">Figure 10A</figureCitation>
). I-L-5 with a large (L 55µm) blade-like distoventral seta (
<figureCitation box="[1238,1373,486,510]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="18.[159,171,1151,1170]" captionTargetBox="[242,1346,302,1118]" captionTargetId="figure-5@18.[242,1346,302,1118]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10: Unionicola (Majumderatax) sp., deutonymph, Mekong River, Vietnam: A – idiosoma, ventral view; B-C – palp; D – I-L-5 and -6. Scale bars – 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396008" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396008/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">Figure 10D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[826,1429,311,1200]" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">Measurements — Idiosoma L/W 447/378; coxal field L/W 225/252; provisional genital plate L/W 37/26, Ac diameter 19-20. Palp: total L 196, dL/H, dL/H ratio: P-1, 12/25, 0.5; P-2, 60/35, 1.7; P-3, 19/34, 0.55; P-4, 65/28, 2.3; P-5, 40/-; dL ratio P- 2/P-4, 0.93; gnathosoma vL 95; chelicera total L 97.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[826,1429,311,1200]" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">
Remarks — In addition to the 
<typeStatus box="[1271,1323,755,779]" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Szalay, 1927" authorityName="Szalay" authorityYear="1927" box="[826,1200,790,814]" class="Arachnida" family="Unionicolidae" genus="Unionicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hankoi">
<emphasis box="[826,1031,790,814]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">Unionicola hankoi</emphasis>
Szalay, 1927
</taxonomicName>
, known from the Palaearctic, the subgenus includes 
<taxonomicName authority="Lundblad, 1969" authorityName="Lundblad" authorityYear="1969" class="Arachnida" family="Unionicolidae" genus="Unionicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crenipalpis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">Unionicola crenipalpis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lundblad O." box="[899,1085,860,884]" pageId="17" pageNumber="409" pagination="289 - 443" refId="ref16169" refString="Lundblad O. 1969 - Indische Wassermilben, hauptsachlich von Hinterindien - Ark. Zool., 22: 289 - 443." type="journal article" year="1969">Lundblad, 1969</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1161,1244,861,884]" name="Myanmar" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">Burma</collectingCountry>
. The combination of a well developed cone-shaped, projections on ventral margin of P-4 (absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lundblad" authorityYear="1969" box="[1266,1420,930,954]" class="Arachnida" family="Unionicolidae" genus="Unionicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crenipalpis">
<emphasis box="[1266,1420,930,954]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">U. crenipalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and one proximomedial serrate seta on P-2 (lacking in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Szalay" authorityYear="1927" box="[909,1019,1000,1024]" class="Arachnida" family="Unionicolidae" genus="Unionicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hankoi">
<emphasis box="[909,1019,1000,1024]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">U. hankoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), easily separates the single deutonymph from the Mekong delta from all other species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vidrine" authorityYear="1993" box="[1110,1269,1071,1095]" class="Arachnida" family="Unionicolidae" genus="Unionicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Majumderatax">
<emphasis box="[1110,1269,1071,1095]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">Majumderatax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Most probably we are dealing with an undescribed species, but since adults are not available, a final decision can not be made.
</paragraph>
